NOTICE — third-party material and EU documents
==============================================

1. EU INSTITUTIONAL DOCUMENTS
   This repository tracks EU legislative documents (Commission proposals, Council compromise
   texts, European Parliament reports, EDPB/EDPS opinions, etc.). Those documents are the work
   of the EU institutions, not of this repository's maintainer, and are NOT covered by the
   CC BY 4.0 licence in the LICENSE file.

   - Legislative texts of the EU are, as a rule, not subject to copyright, and the Commission's
     reuse policy (Decision 2011/833/EU) generally permits reuse of Commission documents with
     attribution. Council and Parliament documents have their own reuse terms.
   - Operative-text EXTRACTS in extracts/ are transcriptions of such documents, provided for
     tracking and diffing. They are reproduced as primary legal source material and carry the
     maintainer's annotations (which ARE under CC BY 4.0); the underlying legal wording is the
     institutions'.

2. LIMITE COUNCIL DOCUMENTS
   Some Council compromise texts (e.g. ST 6406/26, ST 8261/26, ST 9547/26) are marked "LIMITE"
   — a limited-distribution marking (not a security classification). To respect that marking,
   this repository does NOT host the LIMITE PDFs. Instead it:
     - records the document in the register (sources/), and
     - links to authoritative or already-public copies (institutions, or journalists/NGOs that
       have published them), and
     - contains the maintainer's own extracted text and analysis.
   If you hold an authoritative copy, you may keep it locally; do not commit LIMITE binaries to
   this public repository.

3. STAKEHOLDER MATERIAL
   Quotations from regulators, NGOs, law firms and industry are short, attributed, and used for
   identification and commentary. Copyright in those works remains with their authors.
